# Medallion-10: Iteration 17 — Add {10/2} to C1 to populate inner-star--star-v20
#
# Iter 14 baseline (KEPT): composite=0.7842
# Iter 15 (strapwork width 5 alternating): REVERTED, composite=0.6604
# Iter 16 (strapwork width 5 over):       REVERTED, composite=0.6089
#   Both strapwork attempts blocked by bikar #114 (assignStrands rotation
#   non-invariance). Until #114 PR1 lands, no strapwork edits.
#
# Iter 14's warnings[0] (from validation/validation.json):
#   "missing-shapes: 45 ref shapes not found in recon" (cf_delta=+0.0667)
#   But diff-level "missing-shapes" is encoder-vocabulary noise (per iter-14
#   guidance.md and CLAUDE.md tenet 6). Real signal is A6:
#     inner-star--star-v20 MISSING 0/1
#     inner-star--star-v8 MISSING 0/6
#     inner-star--rhombus-v4 MISSING 0/10  (NOTE: iter-14 added {10/3} for this; still 0?)
#     transition--star-v8 MISSING 0/4
#     rosette--star-v8 MISSING 0/2
#     ...11 MISSING + 4 PARTIAL total
#
# Mechanical edit: add `connect every 2 on C1`. The {10/2} on a 10-divided circle
# is a single 10-pointed star (decagram-2) whose outline traces 20 vertices
# (10 outer tips, 10 inner valleys) — exactly inner-star--star-v20 (expected 1).
#
# Secondary effect: the {10/2} edges intersect the existing {10/4}+{10/3} edges
# at additional points in the inner-star zone. After `voids detect` those
# intersections create new sub-faces, some of which may be 4-pointed stars
# (8-vertex, addressing inner-star--star-v8 MISSING 0/6).
#
# Translation table mapping:
# - "A6 inner-star--star-v20 MISSING 0/1" = baseline-shape-missing
#   Fix: connect every 2 on C1 → produces a {10/2} = 10-pointed star
#   whose outline is a 20-vertex polygon when classified by the encoder.
#
# Predicted Δcomposite vs iter 14: +0.03 to +0.06
#   - A6 inner-star--star-v20: MISSING -> PASS (~+0.03 structural rollup)
#   - Possible secondary: inner-star--star-v8 MISSING -> PARTIAL (~+0.01)
#   - rhombus-v4: iter-14 added {10/3} but still MISSING — adding {10/2}
#     creates more intersections that may finally produce the rhombi (~+0.02)
# Predicted Δstructural: 1/18 -> 2/18 or 3/18
# Predicted A2 cv: stays at iter-14's 0.067 (no strapwork added,
#   so assignStrands rotation issue cannot trigger)
# Predicted extras: minimal increase (no band fragments — closed polygon
#   intersections are well-paired by qiyas)

blueprint medallion
  circle C0 center(0,0) radius 100
  divide C0 into 10
  circle C1 center(0,0) radius 30
  divide C1 into 10
  circle Cmid2 center(0,0) radius 50
  divide Cmid2 into 10
  circle Cmid center(0,0) radius 80
  divide Cmid into 10
  repeat at C0 depth 1
    circle center($point) radius 0.3 * $radius
    divide into 10

pattern medallion on medallion
  # Layer 0: Central {10/4} + {10/3} (iter 14) + NEW {10/2} (iter 17)
  # The three decagrams ({10/4}, {10/3}, {10/2}) on C1 produce a dense
  # intersection mesh. {10/2} alone creates the missing star-v20.
  layer 0
    connect every 4 on C1
    connect every 3 on C1
    connect every 2 on C1

  layer 1
    connect every 4 on @0.0
    connect every 4 on @0.1
    connect every 4 on @0.2
    connect every 4 on @0.3
    connect every 4 on @0.4
    connect every 4 on @0.5
    connect every 4 on @0.6
    connect every 4 on @0.7
    connect every 4 on @0.8
    connect every 4 on @0.9

  layer 2
    connect every 3 on Cmid

  layer 3
    connect every 4 on Cmid2

  voids detect

  palette medallion_blue
      deep_navy = #091428
      navy = #0D1B3E
      royal = #1B4F72
      cobalt = #2874A6
      turquoise = #48C9B0

  fill void where sides == 10 color deep_navy
  fill void where sides == 4 color royal
  fill void where sides == 3 color turquoise
  fill void where sides == 20 color navy
  fill void where sides >= 5 color cobalt

  edges color navy width 0.5
